232
00:07:49,369 --> 00:07:50,702
              when you come out 
              with the spatula. 

233
00:07:50,704 --> 00:07:52,637
A little bit of sauce.          
  Parmigiano first.             

234
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:53,905
    Ground beef.                

235
00:07:53,907 --> 00:07:55,273
              A little garlic,  
       a little salt and pepper.

236
00:07:55,275 --> 00:07:56,908
      Parsley.                  
     Mozzarella.                

237
00:07:56,910 --> 00:07:58,910
And then we're gonna go for     
 the ricotta cheese.            

238
00:07:58,912 --> 00:08:00,244
               Nice and light.  
  Mm-hmm.                       

239
00:08:00,246 --> 00:08:01,579
        How many layers of this,
                   three?       

240
00:08:01,581 --> 00:08:02,647
 Three should work.             

241
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:04,582
                [ Chuckles ]    
              Oh, look at that! 

242
00:08:04,584 --> 00:08:06,451
                     ♪♪         

243
00:08:06,453 --> 00:08:09,120
      See those layers in there?
                    Ohh!        

244
00:08:09,122 --> 00:08:10,588
                    Mmm.        
              That's delicious. 

245
00:08:10,590 --> 00:08:12,790
     That's up there with any of
    the best lasagnas there are.

246
00:08:12,792 --> 00:08:14,259
           -Great job.          
           -Thank you.          

247
00:08:14,261 --> 00:08:15,994
    MAN: Meat lasagna ready.    

248
00:08:15,996 --> 00:08:18,529
 We had a huge spike            
    from lasagna.               

249
00:08:18,531 --> 00:08:20,198
    And we had to do a spin-off.

250
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,867
     This is our                
  eggplant lasagna.             

251
00:08:22,869 --> 00:08:25,337
We're gonna start by coating    
the pan with butter,            

252
00:08:25,339 --> 00:08:28,540
butter and breadcrumb           
will help the lasagna not stick.

253
00:08:28,542 --> 00:08:30,541
Add the baked eggplant.         

254
00:08:30,543 --> 00:08:33,812
Add some of the marinara,       
a little bit of the mozzarella, 

255
00:08:33,814 --> 00:08:35,413
and the Parmigiano-Reggiano     
       sauce.                   

256
00:08:35,415 --> 00:08:38,616
We're gonna add a little bit of 
egg wash that has fresh parsley,

257
00:08:38,618 --> 00:08:40,284
basil, salt, and pepper.        

258
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:43,221
And then we add exactly         
  the same layers.              

259
00:08:43,223 --> 00:08:45,423
And a nice breadcrumb           
      topping.                  

260
00:08:45,425 --> 00:08:47,759
  Bake it for about             
 an hour and a half.            

261
00:08:47,761 --> 00:08:51,696
                     ♪♪         

262
00:08:51,698 --> 00:08:53,899
              Eggplant lasagna, 
                table seven.    

263
00:08:53,901 --> 00:08:56,234
The eggplant is one of          
my favorite go-to dishes.       

264
00:08:56,236 --> 00:08:58,703
It's huge. I probably gonna have
to take a nap after this one.   

265
00:08:58,705 --> 00:08:59,971
   It's fantastic.              

266
00:08:59,973 --> 00:09:02,507
   You can taste the saltiness  
       from the Reggiano,       

267
00:09:02,509 --> 00:09:05,243
         very authentic,        
          very Italian.         

268
00:09:05,245 --> 00:09:07,112
Can't make it to Italy?         
Come to DiPasquale's.           

269
00:09:07,114 --> 00:09:09,581
I think you'll get a nice       
little Italian immersion.       

270
00:09:09,583 --> 00:09:11,783
       I'm glad you remember us.
             I mean, it's nice. 

271
00:09:11,785 --> 00:09:12,917
Couldn't forget you, man.       

272
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:15,053
You're good people making       
    great food --               

273
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:17,288
or should it be "great people   
 making great food."            

274
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:20,591
     You agree?                 
  Of course you do.             

275
00:09:20,593 --> 00:09:23,194
                     ♪♪         

276
00:09:23,196 --> 00:09:25,664
        FIERI: Coming up,       
   a ski town spot in Utah...   

277
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:26,931
             Were you snowed in 
             when you made this?

278
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,132
We were doing something.        

279
00:09:28,134 --> 00:09:30,201
    ...taking comfort food...   
      You take that quick right,

280
00:09:30,203 --> 00:09:31,803
               you end up over  
            in Funky Flavortown.

281
00:09:31,805 --> 00:09:34,005
   ...into a new comfort zone.  

282
00:09:34,007 --> 00:09:35,941
            If I came back here,
            I'd have this again.

283
00:09:35,943 --> 00:09:37,108
                     ♪♪         

284
00:09:39,813 --> 00:09:41,345
   I'm here in Prospect Square  
       in Park City, Utah.      

285
00:09:41,347 --> 00:09:43,347
          And I'm right         
     in the thick of things.    

286
00:09:43,349 --> 00:09:45,150
          Back in 2014,         

287
00:09:45,152 --> 00:09:48,019
    I popped into this place    
cranking out what I like to call

288
00:09:48,021 --> 00:09:49,287
         funky comfort.         

289
00:09:49,289 --> 00:09:51,089
             Anything you order 
              will be amazing.  

290
00:09:51,091 --> 00:09:53,091
         And thankfully,        
       nothing's changed.       

291
00:09:53,093 --> 00:09:54,426
               Boneless wings,  
                 table four.    

292
00:09:54,428 --> 00:09:57,895
     This is Sammy's Bistro.    

293
00:09:57,897 --> 00:10:00,698
  What we saw in "Triple-D" was 
       exactly what we got      

294
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:02,166
   when we walked in the door.  

295
00:10:02,168 --> 00:10:04,035
MAN: There's nothing on         
the menu that I've ever had     

296
00:10:04,037 --> 00:10:05,503
that I didn't absolutely love.  

297
00:10:05,505 --> 00:10:07,639
  That's because chef and owner 
           Sam Harris           

298
00:10:07,641 --> 00:10:09,641
      took his fearlessness     
         off the slopes         

299
00:10:09,643 --> 00:10:12,243
and brought it into the kitchen.

300
00:10:12,245 --> 00:10:13,778
                 Do you ski?    
                Do you board?   

301
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:14,812
  Oh, I'm a skier.              

302
00:10:14,814 --> 00:10:16,381
I think media moguls back       
     in the day.                

303
00:10:16,383 --> 00:10:17,382
                Hence the...?   

304
00:10:17,384 --> 00:10:19,050
        Yeah.                   
 When I was younger,            

305
00:10:19,052 --> 00:10:21,252
 we got done skiing             
and I'd cook for my friends.    

306
00:10:21,254 --> 00:10:22,787
     It's a lot                 
 of experimentation.            

307
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:24,856
Just throw something together.  
Sometimes it turns out.         

308
00:10:24,858 --> 00:10:26,057
So this one is one of those.    

309
00:10:26,059 --> 00:10:27,792
       This is                  
a savory chicken bowl.          

310
00:10:27,794 --> 00:10:28,793
           Show me what you got.

311
00:10:28,795 --> 00:10:30,862
A little canola oil.            
      Poblano.                  

312
00:10:30,864 --> 00:10:32,463
       Onions,                  
put a little garlic in,         

313
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:34,666
and then the chicken,           
and then coat it with spices.   

314
00:10:34,668 --> 00:10:36,134
    Yellow curry,               
    garam masala,               

315
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:37,802
      paprika,                  
    onion powder,               

316
00:10:37,804 --> 00:10:38,536
        salt.                   

317
00:10:38,538 --> 00:10:40,004
                And a little    
                black pepper.   

318
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:41,339
Get the spices coating          
    the chicken,                

319
00:10:41,341 --> 00:10:43,541
  and then just hit             
 some water on top.             

320
00:10:43,543 --> 00:10:45,343
    Let it simmer               
 two to three hours.            

321
00:10:45,345 --> 00:10:46,610
        Until it's super tender.

322
00:10:46,612 --> 00:10:47,779
               Now we're going  
                 to make...?    

323
00:10:47,781 --> 00:10:48,413
  Tomatillo aioli.              

324
00:10:48,415 --> 00:10:49,680
                   Hit it.      

325
00:10:49,682 --> 00:10:52,283
It's not a traditional aioli,   
but that's what we call it.     

326
00:10:52,285 --> 00:10:53,618
      Hey, it's your house, man.

327
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:54,686
               You can call it  
              the Easter Bunny. 

328
00:10:54,688 --> 00:10:57,755
Tomatillos, cilantro,           
buttermilk, jalapeño.           

329
00:10:57,757 --> 00:10:59,891
              The little engine 
              that could, huh?  

330
00:10:59,893 --> 00:11:01,158
  Makes it happen.              

331
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,560
             Pro. Look at that. 

332
00:11:02,562 --> 00:11:05,029
I'm going to throw a little     
bit of lime juice in there      

333
00:11:05,031 --> 00:11:07,231
and our house Cajun seasoning.  

334
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:08,499
           The hits keep coming.

335
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:09,901
 Ranch dressing mix.            

336
00:11:09,903 --> 00:11:11,036
             Were you snowed in 
             when you made this?

337
00:11:11,038 --> 00:11:12,503
We were doing something.        
 It was late night.             

338
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:13,704
  Yeah, it was fun.             

339
00:11:13,706 --> 00:11:14,839
             Now we put the bowl
                  together?     

340
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:17,108
 Yep. Jasmine rice.             
We ladle our chicken.           

341
00:11:17,110 --> 00:11:18,776
Some of the tortilla            
   strips on top.               

342
00:11:18,778 --> 00:11:20,578
Make it tall, tall, like        
     your hair.                 

343
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:21,713
                Looking good.   

344
00:11:21,715 --> 00:11:26,317
Cilantro, and finish off        
with the tomatillo aioli.       

345
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:27,318
                That's one of   
             the weirdest dishes

346
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,720
               I've ever seen   
               on "Triple-D."   

347
00:11:29,722 --> 00:11:32,256
             Well, Flavortown --
      You've been to Flavortown?

348
00:11:32,258 --> 00:11:33,391
    Every night.                

349
00:11:33,393 --> 00:11:35,059
           Sometimes on your way
               to Flavortown,   

350
00:11:35,061 --> 00:11:36,127
                 if you take    
              that quick right, 

351
00:11:36,129 --> 00:11:37,729
               you end up over  
            in Funky Flavortown.

352
00:11:37,731 --> 00:11:40,265
             It's a sister city.
     That might be where we are.

353
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:41,466
 Just one more exit,            
      actually.                 

354
00:11:41,468 --> 00:11:43,534
                [ Chuckling ]   
               One more exit.   

355
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:48,139
                     ♪♪         

356
00:11:48,141 --> 00:11:49,607
         Chicken's super tender.

357
00:11:49,609 --> 00:11:51,342
Comfort food at its finest.     

358
00:11:51,344 --> 00:11:54,946
            It is funky comfort.
  I will give you that, brother.

359
00:11:54,948 --> 00:11:57,481
                Mmm! I would,   
              without question, 

360
00:11:57,483 --> 00:12:00,752
            if I came back here,
            I'd have this again.

361
00:12:00,754 --> 00:12:02,687
      The menu                  
 is pretty eclectic.            

362
00:12:02,689 --> 00:12:05,623
It's something that pretty      
much appeals to everyone.       

363
00:12:05,625 --> 00:12:08,026
    One of the things I love    
 about Sammy's is there are lots

364
00:12:08,028 --> 00:12:11,830
     of options for me, like    
  the vegan coconut red curry.  

365
00:12:11,832 --> 00:12:13,498
  So to make the vegan coconut  
           red curry,           

366
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:16,434
    we started with sautéing    
minced garlic and minced ginger,

367
00:12:16,436 --> 00:12:19,437
      add crushed tomatoes,     
     garam masala, turmeric,    

368
00:12:19,439 --> 00:12:22,841
  paprika, kosher salt, cumin,  
          and cayenne.          

369
00:12:22,843 --> 00:12:24,975
        We let that cook        
        for about an hour       

370
00:12:24,977 --> 00:12:26,911
 and blend it until very smooth.

371
00:12:26,913 --> 00:12:29,447
       And at this point,       
 we're gonna add our vegetables.

372
00:12:29,449 --> 00:12:32,183
   Red bell pepper, zucchini,   
            eggplant,           

373
00:12:32,185 --> 00:12:33,918
   yellow onions, and carrots.  

374
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,920
         Let that simmer        
     for another 45 minutes.    

375
00:12:35,922 --> 00:12:37,388
         And then we add        
        the coconut milk,       

376
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:39,190
         which gives it         
       a nice creaminess.       

377
00:12:39,192 --> 00:12:40,658
      And then coconut oil.     

378
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,359
 We plate it over jasmine rice, 

379
00:12:42,361 --> 00:12:44,061
        put a little side       
     of pita bread on there     

380
00:12:44,063 --> 00:12:45,396
and garnish it with green onion.

381
00:12:45,398 --> 00:12:47,732
       Coconut red curry.       

382
00:12:47,734 --> 00:12:50,668
      This is outstanding.      
  The vegetables are so hearty. 

383
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:52,203
      It almost taste like      
     there's meat in there.     

384
00:12:52,205 --> 00:12:54,338
                 It's spicy,    
             but not too spicy. 

385
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:58,209
            It's incredibly rich
         and flavorful, filling.

386
00:12:58,211 --> 00:13:00,812
           Love all the veggies.

387
00:13:00,814 --> 00:13:01,679
         Now what are we making?

388
00:13:01,681 --> 00:13:02,880
  The Chivito club              
      sandwich.                 

389
00:13:02,882 --> 00:13:03,614
                The who club?   

390
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:05,149
  The Chivito club.             

391
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:06,217
 We're going to make            
    the marinade                

392
00:13:06,219 --> 00:13:07,952
for the pork tenderloin --      
     canola oil,                

393
00:13:07,954 --> 00:13:12,824
soy sauce, garlic, ginger,      
cilantro, lime juice.           

394
00:13:12,826 --> 00:13:14,092
     How long is this tenderloin
             going to marinate? 

395
00:13:14,094 --> 00:13:15,359
   45 to an hour.               

396
00:13:15,361 --> 00:13:16,227
                  Grill it.     

397
00:13:16,229 --> 00:13:17,295
    Yeah, medium,               

398
00:13:17,297 --> 00:13:18,830
and let it rest for a minute.   

399
00:13:18,832 --> 00:13:20,899
While we do that, we're         
 gonna make the egg.            

400
00:13:20,901 --> 00:13:23,434
                     ♪♪         

401
00:13:23,436 --> 00:13:24,302
                  Hey, hey!     

402
00:13:24,304 --> 00:13:26,037
                He'll be here   
              all week, folks.  

403
00:13:26,039 --> 00:13:27,104
And it's on a hoagie roll.      

404
00:13:27,106 --> 00:13:29,307
    A little bit                
of the tomatillo aioli.         

405
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:32,844
Lettuce, tomato, pork tenderloin
a little bit of bacon,          

406
00:13:32,846 --> 00:13:34,846
and some spicy mayo.            

407
00:13:34,848 --> 00:13:38,449
                     ♪♪         

408
00:13:38,451 --> 00:13:39,717
     All right.                 
    And the egg.                

409
00:13:39,719 --> 00:13:41,519
     I went to grab the egg,    
      and I turned around,      

410
00:13:41,521 --> 00:13:43,521
    and the egg was missing.    

411
00:13:43,523 --> 00:13:46,190
                     ♪♪         

412
00:13:46,192 --> 00:13:46,858
        Huh?                    

413
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,926
                [ Chuckles ]    

414
00:13:48,928 --> 00:13:50,595
  Where's the egg?              

415
00:13:50,597 --> 00:13:51,596
               It looks good.   
               Let's have it.   

416
00:13:51,598 --> 00:13:52,864
  It's perfect now,             
       right?                   

417
00:13:52,866 --> 00:13:54,999
     We know he loves eggs.     

418
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:57,535
    There it is.                
Throw a little fried egg on top.

419
00:13:57,537 --> 00:13:59,604
    A little more               
  tomatillo aioli.              

420
00:13:59,606 --> 00:14:03,073
                     ♪♪         

421
00:14:03,075 --> 00:14:05,276
                     ♪♪         

422
00:14:05,278 --> 00:14:08,880
    Mmm. Even with egg on there,
          it's a great sandwich.

423
00:14:08,882 --> 00:14:10,281
                    Mmm.        

424
00:14:10,283 --> 00:14:12,149
       Before                   
"Diners, Drive-Ins & Dives,"    

425
00:14:12,151 --> 00:14:16,354
it was like 20th or 25th on     
the list of most popular things.

426
00:14:16,356 --> 00:14:17,955
It's like number two now.       

427
00:14:17,957 --> 00:14:19,691
And I have a feeling            
that in a couple years,         

428
00:14:19,693 --> 00:14:21,826
the seafood cioppino will be    
one of the top-selling things   

429
00:14:21,828 --> 00:14:23,961
on the menu, as well.           

430
00:14:23,963 --> 00:14:26,598
    This may be my new go-to,   
      the seafood cioppino.     

431
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,499
 We throw red onion             
   and garlic in,               

432
00:14:28,501 --> 00:14:30,434
 and let that sauté             
 for a few minutes.             

433
00:14:30,436 --> 00:14:33,437
After that, we reduced          
some merlot red wine down,      

434
00:14:33,439 --> 00:14:34,839
   and then we add              
 our crushed tomato,            

435
00:14:34,841 --> 00:14:38,109
   oregano, basil,              
a little bit of sugar,          

436
00:14:38,111 --> 00:14:41,645
  balsamic vinegar,             
and salt and pepper.            

437
00:14:41,647 --> 00:14:43,581
  Add a little bit              
 of garlic, shrimp,             

438
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:46,517
scallops, and the mussels,      
little neck clams, calamari,    

439
00:14:46,519 --> 00:14:47,785
    and mahimahi,               

440
00:14:47,787 --> 00:14:49,720
 a little white wine            
     and water,                 

441
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:51,388
and our house-made marinara.    

442
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:53,457
Fennel bulb -- a little bit     
of a licorice flavor,           

443
00:14:53,459 --> 00:14:56,060
butter, and we finish it off    
 with some chipotle             

444
00:14:56,062 --> 00:14:57,328
     to give it                 
a little bit of a kick.         

445
00:14:57,330 --> 00:14:59,864
   Just cover that              
  and let it steam.             

446
00:14:59,866 --> 00:15:02,000
Plate it over Jasmine rice.     

447
00:15:02,002 --> 00:15:04,268
              Seafood cioppino, 
                table eight.    

448
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:06,604
          Really tasty,         
   and it's got this chipotle   

449
00:15:06,606 --> 00:15:08,806
   that pops when you eat it.   

450
00:15:08,808 --> 00:15:12,076
  Not over the top,             
but definitely excellent flavor.

451
00:15:12,078 --> 00:15:14,078
I can't wait to eat it,         
so quit talking to me!          

452
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:16,881
     [ Laughs ]                 

453
00:15:16,883 --> 00:15:19,617
     SAM: Once Guy comes in,    
       you're on the map.       

454
00:15:19,619 --> 00:15:22,153
      Next thing you know,      
       line out the door.       

455
00:15:22,155 --> 00:15:23,687
          Unbelievable.         

456
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:25,757
   We're going to open another  
  place out at Kimball Junction 

457
00:15:25,759 --> 00:15:27,558
 called Sammy's Bistro Express. 

458
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:30,561
     Should be really cool.     

459
00:15:30,563 --> 00:15:33,031
         Watch out for this guy.
 When you see him on the slopes,

460
00:15:33,033 --> 00:15:36,033
       if he skis like he cooks,
               take a day off.  

461
00:15:36,035 --> 00:15:38,703
                     ♪♪         

462
00:15:38,705 --> 00:15:41,973
Now coming up, an Italian family
   bringing their classics...   

463
00:15:41,975 --> 00:15:43,841
      I'm a meatball aficionado,
               you know that.   

464
00:15:43,843 --> 00:15:45,776
        ...to the crowds        
       all over Cleveland.      

